<https://w3id.org/ppon/lppo#photometricCentrePositionYDirection> <https://w3id.org/ppon/lppo#hasID> "04-0003" .
# 
# https://w3id.org/ppon/lppo#photometricCentrePositionZDirection
<https://w3id.org/ppon/lppo#photometricCentrePositionZDirection> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual> .
<https://w3id.org/ppon/lppo#photometricCentrePositionZDirection> <https://w3id.org/ppon/bppo#description> "Z position of the point used as origin for photometric measurements and calculations in relation to the middle of the bounding box. Positive values are aligned with the gamma angle 180° (up). Negative values are aligned with the gamma angle 0° (down).  If the light centre point is at the bottom side, then this value is the negative half of the height. See also EN 13032-4:2015."@en .
<https://w3id.org/ppon/lppo#photometricCentrePositionZDirection> <https://w3id.org/ppon/bppo#digitalFormat> "(1E0, mm)" .
<https://w3id.org/ppon/lppo#photometricCentrePositionZDirection> <https://w3id.org/ppon/bppo#hasGUID> "2MDJxTVzv57ALNnXX1bC1W" .
<https://w3id.org/ppon/lppo#photometricCentrePositionZDirection> <https://w3id.org/ppon/bppo#hasName> "photometric centre position z direction"@en .
<https://w3id.org/ppon/lppo#photometricCentrePositionZDirection> <https://w3id.org/ppon/lppo#hasID> "04-0004" .
# 
